   =20
      Pre-revenue banking platform
   =20
 =20

In the consumer tech world it is pretty common for a company to start with =
a popular product but no revenue model. =E2=80=9CWe will build an app to le=
t people share pictures with their friends, for free=E2=80=9D is an idea th=
at can be worth billions of dollars even if it doesn=E2=80=99t make any mon=
ey. Because, you know, at this point, there is a pretty good history of peo=
ple finding ways to make it make money. Ads, mainly. Eventually you get to =
critical mass and you charge companies to advertise to the people sharing p=
ictures with their friends. This does not always work, but it works often e=
nough and in big enough ways that people keep doing it.
You see it less in=C2=A0banking?=C2=A0But here=E2=80=99s this:

[Citigroup Inc.] has been operating a lending platform that connects small =
banks to small businesses whose borrowing needs fall below Citi=E2=80=99s t=
ypical size threshold.
Now it is looking to cash in on the platform, known as Bridge built by Citi=
. It is preparing to sell a majority stake in the venture.
Rohit Mathur, a Citi commercial banker who, along with a colleague, came up=
 with the idea for Bridge, likens the platform to a dating app but for lend=
ing. The Bridge website says it enables small businesses to submit loan pro=
posals to 75 banks which bid to compete. Citi doesn=E2=80=99t do any lendin=
g of its own on the platform, which targets loans of between $100,000 and $=
10mn.
=E2=80=9CFirst thing we always get asked is, =E2=80=98What=E2=80=99s in it =
for Citi?=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D said Mathur, who noted that it has never charge=
d banks or borrowers for access to the platform. =E2=80=9CIf it works out, =
it has the potential to provide equity upside for Citi.=E2=80=9D
Mathur said the stake could be sold in the next few months, though no deal =
is certain, and Citi is likely to retain a share in the start-up after a de=
al closes.

=E2=80=9CIt has never charged banks or borrowers for access to the platform=
,=E2=80=9D but =E2=80=9Cit has the potential to provide equity upside for C=
iti.=E2=80=9D Presumably by one day charging them?

